<div class="media-wrapper"><img decoding="async" src="https://cdn.macstories.net/wwdc_25_bento-1749520947983.png" alt="Source: Apple."><p class="image-caption">Source: Apple.</p></div>
<p id="p2">Every keynote, Apple is well-known for summarizing sections of the presentation with immaculately laid-out bento boxes containing key features. They often serve as good, easily digestible overviews of all the new features for each OS.</p>
<p id="p3">With that in mind, let&rsquo;s take a look at all the bento boxes from today&rsquo;s WWDC 2025 keynote.</p>
<aside class="aside aligncenter aside-narrow" id="aside4"><h2 id="textsniper">TextSniper</h2>

<p></p><center><img decoding="async" src="https://cdn.macstories.net/textsniper_-app_icon-1748888530518.png" width="180" alt=""></center>
<p><strong><a href="https://textsniper.app/?utm_campaign=wwdc2025&amp;utm_source=mac_stories&amp;utm_medium=sponsorship&amp;utm_content=link_post" rel="noopener noreferrer noopener noreferrer">Copy Text and Scan QR Codes with TextSniper</a></strong> from videos, PDFs, images, etc.</p>
</aside><p id="p5"><!--more--></p>
<h1 id="ios">iOS</h1>
<div class="media-wrapper"><img decoding="async" src="https://cdn.macstories.net/wwdc_25_bento_ios-1749519581643.png" alt="Source: Apple."><p class="image-caption">Source: Apple.</p></div>
<div class="media-wrapper"><img decoding="async" src="https://cdn.macstories.net/wwdc_25_bento_ios_2-1749519581507.png" alt="Source: Apple."><p class="image-caption">Source: Apple.</p></div>
<p id="p8">Apple presumably wanted to mention lots of extra features coming to their most popular OS, so they added an extra slide listing a whole raft of new additions. Some that jumped out for me were &lsquo;Custom snooze length for alarms&rsquo;, &lsquo;Select partial text in bubble&rsquo; for Messages, and &lsquo;Adaptive power&rsquo;, which might refer to the rumored AI battery enhancements.</p>
